<p><b>Sir Tom Stoppard</b> <a href="/wiki/Order_of_Merit_(Commonwealth)" title="Order of Merit (Commonwealth)" class="mw-redirect">OM</a>, <a href="/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire" title="Order of the British Empire">CBE</a>, <a href="/wiki/FRSL" title="FRSL" class="mw-redirect">FRSL</a> (born 3 July 1937) is a British <a href="/wiki/Screenwriter" title="Screenwriter">screenwriter</a> and playwright.<sup id="cite_ref-sal_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-sal-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> He has written plays such as <i><a href="/wiki/The_Coast_of_Utopia" title="The Coast of Utopia">The Coast of Utopia</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/Arcadia_(play)" title="Arcadia (play)">Arcadia</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/Rosencrantz_%26_Guildenstern_Are_Dead" title="Rosencrantz &amp; Guildenstern Are Dead" class="mw-redirect">Rosencrantz &amp; Guildenstern Are Dead</a></i>, and <i><a href="/wiki/Rock_%27n%27_Roll_(play)" title="Rock 'n' Roll (play)">Rock 'n' Roll</a></i>. He co-wrote the screenplays for <i><a href="/wiki/Brazil_(film)" title="Brazil (film)">Brazil</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/Shakespeare_in_Love" title="Shakespeare in Love">Shakespeare in Love</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-utop_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-utop-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
